                <note rend="inline" type="source">196.6/1094</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Netherlands Legation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1776</seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Note Verbale</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Netherland Legation has noticed that a bill (S. 314) has been introduced by
                    Senator LaFollette relating to the payment of advance wages and allotments in
                    respect to seamen on foreign vessels and making further provision for carrying
                    out the purpose of the Seamen’s Act, approved March 4, 1915,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d846fn2">38 Stat. 1164.</note> which bill is a copy of the bill
                    introduced during last session by the same Senator and passed by the Senate on
                    April 24, 1928.</p>
                <p>The Royal Legation has the honor to inform the State Department that the remarks
                    made on behalf of the Netherland Government by its note of May 3, 1928, No.
                        1413,<note n="3" xml:id="d846fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1928v01#pg_835">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1928, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 835</ref>.</note> are in the same way
                    applicable to the new bill.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-15">May 15,
                            1929</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
